                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/17.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Vice Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1913</hi>
                        </date>,</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your despatch April 5 regarding exaction by insurrectionary authorities of taxes
                    on mines and other property owned by American citizens. Such taxes should be
                    paid under protest, which protest should so far as possible be made a matter of
                    record in each case. Properly authenticated receipts should be secured for all
                    taxes paid. Americans are entitled however to pay taxes to persons in de facto
                    authority. For principle involved see Moore’s Digest, Volume 1, pages 183, 184;
                    Volume 4, page 12. Department is instructing Embassy to lay matter before
                    appropriate authorities calling attention to the exaction of taxes by
                    insurrectionary forces and stating that this Government will regard payment of
                    such taxes to such persons <pb facs="0849" n="733" xml:id="pg_733"/> exercising
                    de facto authority as completely relieving American citizens from further
                    obligation with reference to taxes so paid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
